# 7. 迷路の先にあるもの

Kanade: Phew...
Kanade: (Mizuki helped remind me about a lot of things today.)
Kanade: (I'm still not sure what kind of song will save Mafuyu, but that's okay...)
Kanade: I just have to keep trying. No matter how long it takes.
Kanade: No, this won't work...
Kanade: It feels like I've taken a step closer, but some things are still missing...
Kanade: It needs to be softer and gentler...
Kanade: Oh...
Kanade: My music box...
Kanade: Right, like this...
Kanade: (It's so gentle and warm, like I'm being wrapped in a blanket. Dad's songs have these qualities.)
Kanade: (Qualities that my songs don't have...)
Kanade: (But what am I missing? How did dad capture these feelings so well...?)
Kanade: (When he made this song, he was...)
Kanade's Father: As long as my music makes you and your mother smile, I'll be more than happy.
Kanade: As long as it made us smile even a little bit...
Kanade: (Dad sang that song because he wanted mom and me to smile...)
Kanade: (So what's my goal? What do I want for Mafuyu?)
Kanade: (I... I just don't want her to disappear...)
Kanade: (No, that's just a personal desire. I want her to stay so that I don't get hurt...)
Kanade: (What do I want her to feel? What do I want her to do?)
Kanade: (I want her to be her the way she wants to be... I think...)
Kanade: (But I don't know who that Mafuyu is. What's going to happen when she does find the “real” her?)
Kanade: *Sigh*...
Kanade: I really wasn't thinking about Mafuyu's best interests, was I...?
Kanade: I'll be stuck in a loop at this rate...
Luka: What is it that you want people to see or realize by hearing this?
Kanade: What do I want people to realize...?
Kanade: What do I want Mafuyu to realize...?
Kanade's Mother: Your father's music always finds a way to make me smile.
Kanade: Oh...
Kanade: (It's that.)
Kanade: (I'm not sure I can put it into words but...)
Kanade: (I want her to be able to feel a lot of different emotions like mom did back then...)
Kanade: I want her to smile...
Kanade: Done...
Kanade: This seems completely different from anything I made before...
Kanade: (What kind of expression will Mafuyu have on her face after listening to this?)
Kanade: (I'm a little nervous...)
Kanade: No...
Kanade: I want all of them to listen to it.
Kanade: <Hello? Are you all here?>
